					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Since we're talking about diskettes and school: back when I was in high school, the only way to turn in programming assignments was via floppy disks. I was always bad at meeting deadlines, so more than once I managed to extend a deadline by saving dummy files using believable names for Delphi and VB projects and intentionally making the disks unreadable using magnets and scratching them with a paper clip. That would buy me up to 2 weeks to code the actual assignment, since the teacher would only be able to tell me about the problem on the next class, and I could only bring the new floppy with the actual code on the one after that. Worked every time.</div>

